The problem of finding a minimum set of boxes to cover the same region as a given set of boxes is a geometric optimization problem, which suggests that it may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem is also related to graph theory, as it involves finding a minimum subset of a set of objects that satisfies certain constraints, which suggests that it may belong to the graph theory (cs.DS) or combinatorics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper mentions that the problem becomes solvable in polynomial time under restrictions on the graph induced by the boxes, which suggests that it may belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper provides approximation algorithms for the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
